.TH DOTMATRIX 1 "March 2026" "dotmatrix 0.5.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dotmatrix \- dotfile management and versioning tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dotmatrix
[\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]
.I command
[\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dotmatrix
is a cross-platform dotfile management tool that indexes configuration files where they live,
without using symlinks. It provides version control through git integration
and supports two backup modes: incremental (content-addressed) and archive (tarballs).
.PP
Supports per-file encryption using the age standard for sensitive files like SSH configs
and credentials.
.PP
Works on Linux, macOS, and Windows.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Increase verbosity. Use \fB\-v\fR for verbose output, \fB\-vv\fR for debug output.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help information.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version information.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS init
Initialize dotmatrix configuration and storage directories. Creates config file,
index, and git repository. Prompts for git identity if not configured globally.
.SS add [\fIoptions\fR] \fIpatterns\fR...
Add file patterns to the tracking list.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-recursive
Recursively add all files in directories, respecting .gitignore files.
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-exclude " " \fIpattern\fR
Exclude files matching pattern (can be specified multiple times).
.TP
.BR \-\-max\-depth " " \fIdepth\fR
Maximum directory depth for recursive scanning.
.TP
.BR \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be added without making changes.
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix add ~/.bashrc
dotmatrix add ~/.config/nvim/**
dotmatrix add /etc/nginx/nginx.conf

# Recursive add (respects .gitignore)
dotmatrix add -r ~/.config/nvim
dotmatrix add -r ~/dotfiles --exclude "*.cache"
dotmatrix add -r ~/.config --max-depth 2 --dry-run
.fi
.RE
.SS remove \fIpatterns\fR...
Remove file patterns from the tracking list.
.SS scan [\fB\-\-yes\fR]
Scan all tracked files and update the index with current metadata (hash, size, mtime).
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-yes
Auto-confirm cleanup of orphaned entries.
.SS backup [\fIoptions\fR]
Backup tracked files to storage. Uses incremental or archive mode based on config.
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-message " " \fImessage\fR
Commit message for git (if enabled).
.TP
.BR \-\-password\-file " " \fIFILE\fR
Read encryption password from file. Required for encrypted files in non-interactive mode.
.TP
.BR \-\-password\-stdin
Read encryption password from stdin. Useful for piping from password managers or scripts.
.PP
The \fBDOTMATRIX_PASSWORD\fR environment variable can also be used as a fallback.
.PP
.RS
.nf
# Basic backup
dotmatrix backup -m "Updated shell config"

# With password for encrypted files
dotmatrix backup --password-file ~/.dotmatrix-pass
echo "mypass" | dotmatrix backup --password-stdin
DOTMATRIX_PASSWORD=secret dotmatrix backup
.fi
.RE
.SS restore [\fIoptions\fR]
Restore files from backup. Shows comparison view and requires confirmation.
.TP
.BR \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be restored without making changes.
.TP
.BR \-\-diff
Show file differences for each file.
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-yes
Auto-confirm restore (still creates safety backup).
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-file " " \fIpattern\fR
Restore only files matching pattern.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-commit " " \fIhash\fR
Restore from specific git commit.
.TP
.BR \-\-password\-file " " \fIFILE\fR
Read decryption password from file. Required for encrypted files in non-interactive mode.
.TP
.BR \-\-password\-stdin
Read decryption password from stdin.
.SS status [\fIoptions\fR]
Show status of tracked files compared to last backup.
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-all
Show all files including unchanged.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quick
Quick mode: compare by size/mtime only (skip hash calculation).
.TP
.BR \-\-json
Output in JSON format for scripting.
.SS list
List all tracked file patterns and exclude patterns.
.SS tui
Launch interactive terminal user interface with three tabs:
.TP
.B Tracked Files
View your backed-up files and their status. Press \fBb\fR to run a backup.
.TP
.B Add Files
Browse your computer to add files to tracking.
.TP
.B Restore
Browse backup history and restore files from previous backups.
.PP
.B Key bindings:
.RS
.TP
.B j/k, Up/Down
Navigate file list
.TP
.B Tab
Switch between tabs
.TP
.B v
View file contents with syntax highlighting (works in all tabs)
.TP
.B b
Run backup (Tracked Files tab)
.TP
.B p
Pull from git remote (Tracked Files tab)
.TP
.B P
Push to git remote (Tracked Files tab)
.TP
.B U
Set git remote URL (Tracked Files tab)
.TP
.B Right/l
Expand folder (Tracked Files) / Enter directory (Add Files)
.TP
.B Left/h
Collapse folder (Tracked Files) / Parent directory (Add Files)
.TP
.B Enter
Add file / Select backup / Restore file(s)
.TP
.B ~
Go to home directory (Add Files tab)
.TP
.B A
Add folder as pattern with /** suffix (Add Files tab)
.TP
.B R
Recursive add - preview and select individual files (Add Files tab)
.TP
.B Space
Select multiple items
.TP
.B a
Type a path manually
.TP
.B Ctrl+A
Select/deselect all (in recursive preview)
.TP
.B d
Stop tracking file
.TP
.B X
Toggle encryption for file (shows [E] indicator)
.TP
.B M
Toggle backup mode (Incremental [I] / Archive [A])
.TP
.B S
Save config and reload without quitting
.TP
.B ?
Show help
.TP
.B q
Quit (saves changes)
.RE
.PP
.B File viewer bindings (when viewing a file):
.RS
.TP
.B j/k, Up/Down
Scroll up/down
.TP
.B PgUp/PgDn
Page up/down
.TP
.B g/Home
Go to top
.TP
.B G/End
Go to bottom
.TP
.B q/Esc
Close viewer
.RE
.PP
.B Status symbols (Tracked Files tab):
.RS
.TP
.B " " (space)
Backed up and unchanged
.TP
.B M
Modified since last backup
.TP
.B +
New, not yet backed up
.TP
.B \-
Deleted from your system
.RE
.PP
.B Restore symbols:
.RS
.TP
.B NEW
File missing locally
.TP
.B CHG
Local file differs from backup
.TP
.B OK
Matches backup
.RE
.PP
.B File indicators:
.RS
.TP
.B [I]
Incremental backup mode (content-addressed, deduped)
.TP
.B [A]
Archive backup mode (compressed tarball)
.TP
.B [E]
Encrypted (requires password for backup/restore)
.RE
.SS gui
Launch native graphical user interface. Same features as TUI with mouse support.
.PP
On Windows, use \fBdmgui.exe\fR for a console-free experience.
.SH ENCRYPTION
Files can be encrypted before backup by adding \fBencrypted = true\fR to the pattern:
.PP
.RS
.nf
tracked_files = [
    "~/.bashrc",
    { path = "~/.ssh/config", encrypted = true },
    { path = "~/.aws/credentials", encrypted = true },
    { path = "~/.gnupg/**", encrypted = true },
]
.fi
.RE
.PP
Encryption uses the \fBage\fR standard (age-encryption.org), making backups compatible
with the \fBage\fR CLI tool for manual decryption if needed.
.SS Interactive Mode (TUI/GUI)
You will be prompted for a password when backing up or restoring encrypted files.
.SS Non-Interactive Mode (CLI/Scripts/Cron)
Provide the password using one of these methods (in priority order):
.TP
.B 1. --password-stdin
Read from stdin. Good for scripts and password managers.
.RS
.nf
echo "mypassword" | dotmatrix backup --password-stdin
pass show dotmatrix | dotmatrix backup --password-stdin
.fi
.RE
.TP
.B 2. --password-file FILE
Read from a file. Recommended for cron jobs.
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix backup --password-file ~/.dotmatrix-pass
# Make sure to restrict permissions:
chmod 600 ~/.dotmatrix-pass
.fi
.RE
.TP
.B 3. DOTMATRIX_PASSWORD environment variable
Fallback option.
.RS
.nf
export DOTMATRIX_PASSWORD="mypassword"
dotmatrix backup
.fi
.RE
.SS Example Cron Job
.PP
.RS
.nf
# Daily backup at 2am
0 2 * * * /usr/bin/dotmatrix backup --password-file ~/.dotmatrix-pass -m "Scheduled backup"
.fi
.RE
.SH GIT SYNC
Backups can be synced to a remote git repository using push/pull.
.SS Configuration
Add \fBgit_remote_url\fR to your config.toml:
.PP
.RS
.nf
git_remote_url = "https://github.com/user/dotfiles.git"
# or
git_remote_url = "git@github.com:user/dotfiles.git"
.fi
.RE
.SS TUI Key Bindings
.TP
.B p
Pull from remote
.TP
.B P
Push to remote
.TP
.B U
Set or change remote URL
.SS GUI
Use the Pull/Push buttons in the status bar. If no remote is configured,
a "Set Remote..." button appears instead.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is stored in the config directory (see FILES section):
.PP
.RS
.nf
# Optional: Custom backup location
# data_dir = "~/Dropbox/dotmatrix"

# Git remote for sync
# git_remote_url = "https://github.com/user/dotfiles.git"

git_enabled = true
backup_mode = "incremental"  # or "archive"

tracked_files = [
    "~/.bashrc",
    "~/.config/nvim/**",
    "~/.config/dotmatrix/*",
    # Encrypted files
    { path = "~/.ssh/config", encrypted = true },
]

exclude = [
    "**/*.log",
    "**/node_modules/**",
]
.fi
.RE
.SS BACKUP MODES
.TP
.B incremental
Files are stored by SHA256 hash in content-addressed storage.
Provides automatic deduplication. Best for frequent backups.
.TP
.B archive
Files are stored as compressed tarballs with timestamps.
Best for occasional snapshots.
.SH FILES
Default paths vary by platform:
.SS Linux
.TP
.I ~/.config/dotmatrix/config.toml
Configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/dotmatrix/
Data directory (index, storage, archives, git).
.SS macOS
.TP
.I ~/Library/Application Support/dotmatrix/config.toml
Configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/Library/Application Support/dotmatrix/
Data directory.
.SS Windows
.TP
.I %APPDATA%\\dotmatrix\\config.toml
Configuration file.
.TP
.I %LOCALAPPDATA%\\dotmatrix\\
Data directory.
.SS Data Directory Contents
.TP
.I index.json
File metadata index.
.TP
.I storage/
Content-addressed backup storage (incremental mode).
.TP
.I archives/
Tarball backup storage (archive mode).
.TP
.I README.md
Auto-generated backup summary with commit history.
.TP
.I .git/
Git repository for version control.
.SS Other
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/dotmatrix/restore-backups/
Safety backups created before restore operations.
.TP
.I ~/.dotmatrix-pass
Suggested location for password file (remember to chmod 600).
.SH PATTERN MATCHING
.B dotmatrix
supports glob patterns for file matching:
.PP
.RS
.nf
~/.bashrc              # Single file
~/.config/*            # All files in directory
~/.config/**           # All files recursively
~/.config/**/*.lua     # All .lua files recursively
.fi
.RE
.PP
The \fB~\fR prefix expands to the user's home directory on all platforms.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic workflow
.PP
.RS
.nf
# Initialize
dotmatrix init

# Add files to track
dotmatrix add ~/.bashrc ~/.zshrc

# Scan to index files
dotmatrix scan

# Create backup
dotmatrix backup -m "Initial backup"

# Check status
dotmatrix status

# Restore (interactive)
dotmatrix restore
.fi
.RE
.SS Encrypted files
.PP
.RS
.nf
# In config.toml:
tracked_files = [
    { path = "~/.ssh/config", encrypted = true },
]

# Interactive backup (prompts for password)
dotmatrix tui

# Scripted backup with password file
dotmatrix backup --password-file ~/.dotmatrix-pass

# Restore encrypted files
dotmatrix restore --password-file ~/.dotmatrix-pass
.fi
.RE
.SS Automated backups with cron
.PP
.RS
.nf
# Create password file
echo "your-secure-password" > ~/.dotmatrix-pass
chmod 600 ~/.dotmatrix-pass

# Add to crontab (crontab -e)
0 2 * * * /usr/bin/dotmatrix backup --password-file ~/.dotmatrix-pass -m "Daily backup"
.fi
.RE
.SS Preview restore changes
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix restore --dry-run --diff
.fi
.RE
.SS Custom backup location
.PP
.RS
.nf
# In config.toml:
data_dir = "D:/Backups/dotmatrix"  # Windows
data_dir = "~/Dropbox/dotmatrix"   # Sync via cloud
.fi
.RE
.SS Git sync
.PP
.RS
.nf
# In config.toml:
git_remote_url = "git@github.com:user/dotfiles.git"

# Or set via TUI (press U)

# Push backups to remote
dotmatrix tui  # then press P

# Pull from remote (e.g., on new machine)
dotmatrix tui  # then press p
.fi
.RE
.SS Verbose output
.PP
.RS
.nf
dotmatrix -v backup
dotmatrix -vv status
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred.
